      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HIS FERNANDO (1) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing fourth (19.98) last time in a Grade 5 at Gunnedah. Form at the trip sound including two wins. Rates on top in this line up. DANIEL KEEPING (2) has missed the frame the last couple but was a Grade 5 winner three back (23.09) at Dubbo over 400m. With a good start should be able to take advantage of the low draw. Expected to do much better this time. SHERRY NOT BERRY (8) has a moderate overall strike-rate. Better run when finding the frame last time though, finishing third (22.75) at this track. Form at the trip sound including four wins. Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from an outside draw. Leading chance. REGGAE ETHICS (3) can fill a top-three spot.",
